# Title

This class represents a specdific book being available for sale to Customers, either
in eBook or Print format, or both. Margaret Michell's classic novel "Gone
With The Wind" is an example title. The novel is available in both eBook 
and Print media. Tedchncially, each new edition of a Book is a different title,
but WebBooks doesn't are about the relationship of one edition to another, 
so they will only offer new editions as different titles that are offered for sale.

◇

attributes:
    title:
        name: "title"
        details: The title of the work, as assigned by the author.
        rules: unconstrained
    author:
        name: "author"
        details: |
            The name of the recognized author(s) of the work. While technically 
            there can be many authors on a signle title and the same person can be an 
            author on many different titles, for customer searches, a simple substring 
            mach is sufficient so this attribute is not strictly normalized.
        rules: unconstrained
    subject:
        name: "subject"
        details: |
            The subject matter(s) covered in the work. While technically there can 
            be many subjects in a single title and the same subject can apply to many 
            different title, for customer seraches, a simple substring match is sufficient so 
            this attribute is not strictly normalized.
        rules: unconstrained
    year:
        name: "copyright year"
        details: |
            The year the work has copyrighted. For works that have passed 
            out of copyright or where never copyrighted, the value will be "public domain" 
        rules: either a whole year no earlier than 1780 and no later than this year, or public domain

associations:

    - name: "Sold as"
      from_multiplicity: "1"
      to_class_key: 01_order_fulfillment/medium
      to_multiplicity: "0..2"

    - name: "Obtained from"
      from_multiplicity: "any"
      to_class_key: 01_order_fulfillment/publisher
      to_multiplicity: "1"

states:

  Exists:
    details: The Title is in the system.

events:

    "«new»":
        details: Create this title.
        parameters:
            - name: title
              source: somewhere
            - name: author
              source: somewhere
            - name: subject
              source: somewhere
            - name: year
              source: somewhere
            - name: publisher
              source: somewhere

    "Replenish":
        details: Items of the title are being added to the inventory.
        parameters:
            - name: print medium
              source: somewhere
            - name: qty
              source: somewhere


actions:

    Initialize:
        details: Add a new title to the system.
        requires:
            - year is consistent with the range of .copyright year
        guarantees:
            - |
                one new Title exists with:
                    .title == title
                    .author == author
                    .subject == subject
                    .copyright year == year
                    this Medium linked to its Publisher via Obtained From

    RequestReplenish:
        details: Request more inventory.
        guarantees:
            - replenish ( Print Medium, qty) has been signaled for linked Publisher via Obtained from

transitions:

    - {from: "", event: "«new»", to: "Exists", action: "Initialize"}
    - {from: "Exists", event: "Replenish", to: "Exists", action: "RequestReplenish"}
